    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          Is this book for beginners or men who've already worked on themselves?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Both. Whether you're just waking up to how soft you've gotten or you've been grinding for years, these stories will still call you out. Nobody's excuse-proof.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          Is this just motivational fluff?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">No. Every chapter is a real, documented, verifiable story — no composites, no fiction. This isn't "believe in yourself." This is undeniable proof that your excuse has already been disproven by someone with less than you.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          How is this different from other motivational books?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Most motivational content wants you to feel good for twenty minutes. This book is built to make you feel exposed — because that's what actually produces change, not a temporary high.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          Is it practical or just stories?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Both. Every story ends with a direct, specific lesson and something you can act on tomorrow morning. No abstract theory, no fluff.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-question">
          How long is the book?
          <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M12 5v14M5 12h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
          </span>
        </summary>
        <p class="faq-answer">Every chapter is short and brutal — no filler. You can read it in a weekend, but the stories will sit with you a lot longer than that.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item">
